OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA fine, dry and locally warm
OL,6,Fday for the bulk of the area with
OL,7,Fsunny spells building into the
OL,8,Fafternoon. However some early showers
OL,9,Fmay appear across Argyll. Light winds.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FA dry night with clear
OL,12,Fspells, though lower cloud building
OL,13,Fthrough the central Belt overnight.
OL,14,FWinds light and variable in direction.
OL,15,
OL,16,CMonday:FAnother generally fair days
OL,17,Fweather in prospect with most dry with
OL,18,Fperiods of sunshine widespread through
OL,19,Fthe morning, before turning hazy from
OL,20,Fthe west during the afternoon. Winds
OL,21,Flight.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
